The paper deals with distributed algorithms for dynamic networks, which involves topics such as distributed computing (cs.DC), distributed systems (cs.DS), network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI), algorithms (cs.AL), and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper's focus on distributed algorithms and dynamic networks makes cs.DC and cs.DS the most likely categories. The use of graph theory and algorithms to solve problems such as coloring, matching, and independent set also suggests cs.AL and cs.GT as likely categories.
